
/*
 * 1. `@.arguments` – Finds the first ancestor node named [.arguments] in the hierarchy.
 * 2. `*` – Retrieves all child nodes of the [.arguments] node.
 * 3. `name` – Filters out all nodes not having the name [name] from the previously retrieved children, returning all [name] nodes that are direct children of [.arguments].
 */

.:x:@.arguments/*/name